com.day.cq.dam.scene7

Interface Scene7Service

  • Deprecated. 
    This interface might be removed in the future. Please change your code so that it uses Scene7Service.

    @Deprecated
public interface Scene7Service
    The Scene7Service provides methods for interacting with the official Scene7 API.

      • getCompanyMembership

        java.lang.String getCompanyMembership(ResourceResolver resourceResolver,
                                      java.lang.String userHandle,
                                      java.lang.String email,
                                      java.lang.String password,
                                      java.lang.String region)
        Deprecated. 
        Returns a JSON representation of the company membership information provided by Scene7. The information include a company handle, a company name and an asset root path.

        For example:
        {
        handle: 'jlkj98',
        name: 'Acme Ltd.',
        rootPath: '/MyAssets'
        }

        Parameters:
        resourceResolver - resource resolver used to access Scene7 configuration
        userHandle - Unique user handle
        email - E-Mail address
        password - Password
        region - Region of the Scene7 service
        Returns:
        A JSON string

      • uploadFile

        @Deprecated
java.lang.String uploadFile(java.lang.String path,
                                        java.lang.String email,
                                        java.lang.String password,
                                        java.lang.String region,
                                        java.lang.String userHandle,
                                        java.lang.String companyHandle,
                                        java.lang.String rootPath,
                                        ResourceResolver resolver)
        Deprecated. Please use the uploadFile method from the Scene7UploadService instead.
        Uploads a file at a given repository path to the Scene7 server.
        Parameters:
        path - Path to the file in the repository
        email - E-Mail address
        password - Password
        region - Region of the Scene7 service
        userHandle - Unique user handle
        companyHandle - Unique company handle
        rootPath - Scene7 root path to upload the file to
        resolver - Sling ResourceResolver
        Returns:
        String 'success' if upload finished successfully or a representation of the job handle if upload failed.
